# oftchatbot guidance

- **MVP package:** root `pnpm type-check`, `pnpm lint`, and `pnpm build` in `oftcore` do **not** include oftchatbot. After substantive changes, run from the monorepo root: `pnpm type-check:chatbot`, `pnpm lint:chatbot`, and `pnpm build:chatbot`.
- The primary deterministic assistant is **Lumi**. A secondary persona, **Fox**, may wrap Lumi replies using OpenAI for tone only.
- Always preserve deterministic business decisions from Lumi (intent, state transitions, guardrails, handoff triggers, booking decisions).
- Main Lumi logic lives in `src/lib/lumi/`:
  - `intents.ts`, `entities.ts`, `guardrails.ts`, `copy.ts`, `state-machine.ts`, `telemetry.ts`, `config/clinic.ts`
- Fox conversational wrapper lives in `src/lib/fox/` and must be optional with safe fallback to deterministic Lumi text.
- WhatsApp integration enters via `src/app/api/waha/webhook/route.ts`.
- Contact/session persistence is in `src/lib/contact-profile/store.ts` (including `lumi_sessions`).
- Scheduling APIs are `src/app/api/slots/route.ts` and `src/app/api/book/route.ts`.
- Keep clinical safety guardrails: no diagnosis/prescription/personalized medical conduct.
- Urgency triggers (pain, trauma, sudden vision loss, flashes/sombras, chemical exposure) must prioritize emergency guidance and stop scheduling.
- Handoff to human for pricing/insurance, cancellation/reschedule, explicit human request, and persistent validation failures.
- Any user-visible text must be linguistically reviewed before delivery.
- Always fix grammar, spelling, punctuation, and accentuation (PT-BR when the text is in Portuguese).
- When changing dialogs or state machine behavior, update and run `tests/lumi/dialogs.spec.ts`.
- Destructive actions in UI (delete/clear/reset) must use shadcn `AlertDialog` confirmation; avoid `window.confirm`.
